title: Shared credReader + _pendingIdx race breaks multi-profile reload
updated_at: "2026-07-15T04:40:25Z"
---
## Problem
`loadCredentials` uses a single shared `credReader` with one `_pendingIdx`. Concurrent loads (stagger timer, Refresh, `autoRefresh` firing multiple due profiles, or rediscover mid-flight) overwrite `_pendingIdx` and/or interleave `onNewData` callbacks. A response for profile A can be applied to profile B; the original profile can stay `loading: true` forever.

## Location
contents/ui/ProfileController.qml:360-367

## Suggested fix
Key pending work by the full command/sourceName (or a request id encoded in the source), map `onNewData(sourceName)` → profile id, and reject stale replies after rediscover/profile list replacement. Prefer a per-request queue: only one `connectSource` outstanding, or encode `idx`/`id` into a unique source string and parse it back.

## Source
Review ff0a2eec Issue 1 — primary root cause of “reloading doesn’t work properly”